Add a few spec and a sample pdf for Identity-V encoding support.

* spec/encoding_spec.rb

  Add specs for Identity-V encoding,
  which are the same as specs for Identity-H encoding other than encoding name.

* spec/meta_spec.rb

  Add a spec for Identity-V encoding,
  which uses spec/data/vertical-text-in-identity-v.pdf.

* spec/data/vertical-text-in-identity-v.pdf

  Simple exmaple for vertical text in Identity-V encoding.

Add initial support for Identity-V encoding.

This is a simple fix that enables the access to texts in Identity-V
encoding.  Identity-V encoding is vertical version of Identity-H and the
mapping is the same as for Identity-H (See Table 118 in PDF
32000-1:2008).

This change dosen't distinguish between Identity-H and Identity-V
(because thier mapping is the same).
But it would be better to support to know whether the targetd text is in
horizontal layout or in vertical layout)

commit_list.message:
Add initial support for Identity-V encoding.

This is a simple fix that enables the access to texts in Identity-V
encoding.  Identity-V encoding is vertical version of Identity-H and the
mapping is the same as for Identity-H (See Table 118 in PDF
32000-1:2008).

encoding.  Identity-V encoding is vertical version of Identity-H and the

commit_list.message:
Fix: no outline found with PDFs

ttOutline() (in org.ebookdroid.droids.mupdf.codec.MuPdfOutline)
fails to find any outline if the argument `outline` is negative.

The JNI part of org.ebookdroid.droids.mupdf.codec.MuPdfOutline had
the following code:

    return (jlong) (long) doc->outline;

But this returns negative value if the most significant bit
of outline handle is 1, because `sizeof long` is 4 (32 bit)
and outline handler itself is a 32-bit pointer.
